.TH "pciehp_unconfigure_device" 9 "pciehp_unconfigure_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pciehp_unconfigure_device \- remove PCI devices below a hotplug bridge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pciehp_unconfigure_device
.BI "(struct controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "bool presence "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
PCIe hotplug controller
.IP "presence" 12
whether the card is still present in the slot;
true for safe removal via sysfs or an Attention Button press,
false for surprise removal
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Unbind PCI devices below a hotplug bridge from their drivers and remove
them from the system.  Safely removed devices are quiesced.  Surprise
removed devices are marked as such to prevent further accesses.
